[normal]Financial Impact[bold]"Sadly this is the system we have inherited. A system that allowed some families who were living in areas with incredibly high rents, to claim over £100,000 a year in housing costs."
[normal]Lord Freud, Welfare Reform Minister[bold], 31 October 2012[bold]Regarding the second request, in August 2010, our records show that there were fewer than 5 housing benefit recipients receiving over £1,916 per week (equivalent to around £100,000 per year assuming the recipient remains on benefit for a continuous year). 
